26/07/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU foreign ministers are meeting Monday (26 July) in Brussels to discuss the situation in the Western Balkans.
Kosovo and the reform of local institutions in the province are expected to be of special interest.
Having recently visited Serbia-Montenegro, Dutch Foreign Minister Bernard Bot and French counterpart Michel Barnier will brief the ministers.
Recent problems in Macedonia related to the planned decentralisation are also on the agenda.
(B92, Beta - 25/07/04)
